rComments: One of the best profs at UTSC. He's also just a great guy to talk to about everything from books to movies to life in general. Hi marking is a little tough but his feedback will definitely help you improve.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Great Prof! If you have any questions or if you simply want someone to talk to crack jokes with, he is your guy. Fair marker and gives many extra credit opportunities. Head's up: if you're planning to look for him during office hours, be there early, talk to him after class or bring something to keep you pre-occupied. You'll be there for a while.

He has passion for the source material and is always super fun in class. His syllabus was really diverse. His exams are really fair and studying from his lecture slides alone is enough to get you a solid C. I had an issue with submitting an essay and helped me out, and he's very understanding of what it's like to be a student.
The class is very fun and the prof is super funny and helpful.
If you saw him on the street you'd think he was either an English or Physics professor

His final was extremely fair. Don't miss any lectures, look over his slides, know the poems, and you'll do very well. He's a very fair prof. Funny and easygoing on top of that. He just makes you feel a little better about life in general.

Best Prof I've had all semester. He was just so pleasant to be around, really super nice, fun and made me actually want to attend his lectures. And I was quite sad when it came to the last lecture because I knew I would seriously miss his class. If you have the option of having him as your prof, DO NOT miss out!
Fantastic teacher. The best English teacher I had ever come across

Dr. Tysdal is enthusiastic, encouraging, and incredibly kind.  He opens your eyes to the magic of poetry, and welcomes multiple interpretations.  His lectures are occasionally unstructured, but he does not demand a whole lot, so he's incredibly fair.  And he's just the sweetest.

Excellent class, I attended every class even though they weren't necessarily mandatory. Really interesting lectures, probably my favourite English prof at the school. He was able to create class discussions which is normally hard in a class that size. Very helpful and understanding with grading.

His lectures are always very informative and entertaining. I wish that there was more explanation of the theory in addition to the application to the stories read in class. He's a great professor, and he's also super helpful!
Awesome class! Tysdal gives great lectures and he's up to date with pop culture especially the use of those memes!

He's a great professor.  His lectures are fun and engaging and he's very approachable.  Some people in the class were rude, talking during lectures all the time though...I wish he'd been sterner and just told them to shut up or get out already.  But I guess he's too nice for that.

Excellent. Extremely funny in a thought-provoking upside-down-mind kinda way. He teaches the sort of class you walk away from with something extra. Can lack clarity, but not to a disappointing degree. Very approachable, caring, fun. Approach his class as a rare opportunity to hone a passion, not as academic fact regurgitation,  latter = struggle.
Mr. T is an marvelously creative dude. I mean, this man has enormous brainpower. The stuff he makes you think about transcends the macademia nutshell. Seriously, he's one in a million.

Yes, he is clever and funny, he has a laugh that is contagious... But I don't go to class to laugh or to keep my head tilted up reading a powerpoint which he recites back to us to quickly to jot anything down. When I leave class I wonder what I've learned - because I still have to go home and pull up powerpoint to write it down. His classes are OK.
I already think he is amazing and i've only been in his class twice. He is so kind and clear and funny and i know this semester will be a blast :)

He's HILARIOUS and super nice. ONly thing I wish he didn't use powerpoint slides or read from the text book too much because what he says that's beyond text book material and powerpoint slides is really brilliant!
Funny & Engaging Prof & Good Speaker
Really fun professor. He is very passionate and approachable.
